 --------------------------------------------------
 
 
 JS is used in browser-envi to bring any interactivity to HTML page
 on user/browser events.
 
 JS brings any functionality to web-page by using Web APIs
 
 
 JS             HTML
    <--------->
      Web APIs   ----------> provided by 'browsers' based on w3c standards


using DOM APIs

--> can create/retreive/update/delete HTML elements      
--> can change element's style
--> can change eleemnt's attributes values
--> can change text content of any elemet
--> can create RICH UI components


using XHR API ( AJAX )

--> communicate with server asyc , update results in existing page

using Timer API

--> time func

some HTML5 Web APIS

-> canvas
-> audio/video
-> localStorage
-> geo
-> web sockets
-> WebGL

